# The native dos-hook fast-path binary lands HERE when a per-platform wheel is built
# (docs/286): `scripts/build_wheels.py` drops exactly one `dos-hook[.exe]` per arch
# into this dir before `python -m build`, and the wheel ships it as package data
# (pyproject `[tool.setuptools.package-data] dos = ["_bin/dos-hook*"]`).
#
# Unlike the PLUGIN's binaries (claude-plugin/bin/, which MUST be committed because a
# plugin ships as its git tree — docs/125 GHF4), the WHEEL's binary is BUILT by CI and
# bundled into the artifact, so it is a release artifact, NOT committed to the kernel
# source tree. A clean checkout has NO binary here and `dos.hook_binary.native_hook_binary()`
# returns None → the CLI falls through to the Python hook verb (the docs/100 fallback).
#
# Ignore the binaries; keep this .gitignore so the dir exists in the tree (the locator
# + the package-data glob both reference it).
dos-hook
dos-hook.exe
